# Server
PORT=8080
DATA_DIR=/data

# Consistent SQLite snapshots (PD-33). All optional — sensible defaults below.
# Snapshots land in BACKUP_DIR (default <DATA_DIR>/backups) so whatever ships the
# data volume off-box (Hyper Backup today) carries a WAL-consistent copy.
# BACKUP_CRON=0 3 * * *          # schedule (default 03:00 daily)
# BACKUP_RETAIN_DAYS=14          # prune snapshots older than N days
# BACKUP_DIR=/data/backups       # output dir
# BACKUP_EXTRA_DB_PATHS=         # comma-separated extra DBs to snapshot (e.g. Sortie's .sortie.db)

# Set to 1 on prod: if agent_tickets is empty on boot (e.g. a fresh/wiped
# volume), self-seed the committed baseline from tickets.seed.json. No-op once
# the board has any tickets. Leave unset in dev.
SEED_ON_BOOT=1

# Agent Dashboard — GitHub sync. Two directions, each gated on its own token; each
# is a no-op (logs a line) when unset, so a partial setup boots cleanly. The app
# container has normal outbound (default bridge), so no egress/squid change needed.
#
# PD-165 (read): READ-ONLY token (Issues: Read on the sortie repos). Polls each
# linked issue's sortie:* labels → derived board status (in_progress/in_review/
# completed) + agent state.
# GITHUB_READ_TOKEN=
#
# PD-164 (write): WRITE-scoped token (Issues: Read and write on the sortie repos).
# For tickets in the Queued lane, ensures a sortie:queued GitHub issue exists
# (creating + linking one when absent). Can be the same fine-grained PAT as the
# read token with write added, or a separate one.
# GITHUB_WRITE_TOKEN=

# agent-worker (D-044, D-045): runs as a SEPARATE, egress-hardened container with its OWN
# env file — NOT this one (ANTHROPIC_API_KEY must stay out of the web process). See
# ops/agent-worker/agent-worker.env.example.

# Music Tracker — see Widgets/Music Tracker/PROJECT.md for details
DJ_LIBRARY_PATH=/library
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET=
SPOTIFY_REFRESH_TOKEN=
SPOTIFY_PLAYLIST_ID=
LIDARR_URL=http://nas.local:8686
